TY  - JOUR
T1  - Airline Buyout: Evolutionary Systems Design and Problem Restructuring in Group Decision and Negotiation
AU  - Shakun, Melvin F.
Y1  - 1991/10/01
PY  - 1991
DA  - 1991/10/01
N1  - doi: 10.1287/mnsc.37.10.1291
DO  - 10.1287/mnsc.37.10.1291
T2  - Management Science
JF  - Management Science
JO  - Management Science
SP  - 1291
EP  - 1303
VL  - 37
IS  - 10
PB  - INFORMS
N2  - We discuss problem restructuring involving evolution of the problem representation in group decision and negotiation support systems. We develop the evolutionary systems design (ESD) approach to restructuring involving a heuristic controls/goals/values referral process and other domain-independent methodological knowledge, such as constraint relaxation, contingency planning, coalition formation and flexible goal target. These ideas are applied to multiple problem restructuring in a scenario motivated by labor-management negotiations and buyout in the airline industry, in particular, a composite of negotiations at Eastern Airlines, TWA and UAL.
AB  - We discuss problem restructuring involving evolution of the problem representation in group decision and negotiation support systems. We develop the evolutionary systems design (ESD) approach to restructuring involving a heuristic controls/goals/values referral process and other domain-independent methodological knowledge, such as constraint relaxation, contingency planning, coalition formation and flexible goal target. These ideas are applied to multiple problem restructuring in a scenario motivated by labor-management negotiations and buyout in the airline industry, in particular, a composite of negotiations at Eastern Airlines, TWA and UAL.
